                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d368">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Pan American Airways, Inc./476:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caracas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-06-12T18:00:00-04:30"
                            >June 12, 1929—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>61. Department’s 18, May 25, 3 p.m. Foreign Office in a note dated today
                    transmits without comment letter from Minister of Fomento, also of today,
                    granting permission for one more flight “with official correspondence”.</p>
                <p>… I therefore suggest the Legation be instructed to repeat request for temporary
                    operating permit.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
